solution: ```class LUPrefix {
    private boolean[] uploaded;
    private int longestPrefix;
    private int n;

    public LUPrefix(int n) {
        this.n = n;
        this.uploaded = new boolean[n + 2];
        this.longestPrefix = 0;
    }

    public void upload(int video) {
        uploaded[video] = true;
        while (longestPrefix + 1 <= n && uploaded[longestPrefix + 1]) {
            longestPrefix++;
        }
    }

    public int longest() {
        return longestPrefix;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1) amortized per upload, O(1) per longest
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a boolean array to track uploads and a single counter that advances only when the next expected video arrives, ensuring minimal CPU cycles and memory traffic.

